Rebuild the client and mtk-request components for the NALA locksmith website.


PROJECT CONTEXT

    GitHub: NYCMEL/nala-website
    Stack: Bootstrap 5, jQuery 3.7.1, Material Icons, local vendor files
    wc-include (js/_wc.js): loads HTML fragments async via jQuery Ajax,
        activates <script> tags via _activateScripts()
    wc.publish() / wc.subscribe() = pub/sub (PubSub.js)
    wc.log() = dev console logger
    RULE: every wc.publish() must be preceded by wc.log() of what is being published


DIRECTORY STRUCTURE

    client/
        index.html
        client.html
        js/
            client.js
            client.config.js
            mtk-request.js
            mtk-request.config.js
        css/
            client.scss          (@import "../../css/nala.scss")
            mtk-request.scss


FILE: client/index.html

    Standalone test page. Loads vendor CSS/JS and wc infra, then:
        <script src="client/js/client.js">   MUST come BEFORE the wc-include div
        <wc-include href="client/client.html"/> inside a div


FILE: client/client.html

    Two sections:

    1. Client profile UI
        No breadcrumb.
        Sticky header bar (id="editModeBar", display:none by default):
            position:sticky, top:0, inside .client-container
            margin: -24px -24px 0 -24px to bleed to container edges
            light blue gradient background, box-shadow
            inner div: width:100%, flex, space-between
            LEFT: NALA (bold, uppercase, large, blue) + chevron_right icon + "Business in the Box" (small, gray)
            RIGHT: "Review" label (clickable) + toggle switch + "Edit" label (clickable) + "Save Changes" button
            "Review" and "Edit" labels set toggle.checked and dispatch change event on click
            "Save Changes" button: hidden until edit mode first activated, stays visible after
        .client-layout with margin-top:25px
        Main content: logo, name, rating, badges, share button, stats, tabs,
            about, business hours, payment methods, social media, top pro status
        Sidebar: contact card (priceText + "Need a Hand?" button, no "View project details" link),
            guarantee card (verified_user icon inline with title "Our Guarantee")

    2. mtk-request modal dialog inlined directly — NOT as nested wc-include
        jQuery's $.html() does not trigger connectedCallback on custom elements
        Hidden input: <input type="hidden" class="nala-uid" name="nalaUID" value="">
        Email input has NO required attribute (only name has required)

    Script tags at bottom (run by _activateScripts after injection):
        client/js/mtk-request.config.js
        client/js/mtk-request.js
        client/js/client.config.js


FILE: client/js/client.config.js

    var config = {
        nalaUID: "U12345",    // identifies the client when submitting requests
        editable: true,       // when defined (true or false), shows the edit header bar
        business: { name, logo, rating, ratingText, reviewCount, isTopPro, isOnline },
        stats: [ { icon, text, type } ],
        contact: { priceText, ctaButton },
        guarantee: { title: "Our Guarantee", text, learnMoreLink },
        tabs: [],
        about: { description, readMoreLink },
        businessHours: { title, text },
        paymentMethods: { title, methods },
        socialMedia: { title, links: [ { platform, icon, url } ] },
        topProStatus: { title, description, years: [] }
    }
    client(config);   // call at the very end


FILE: client/js/client.js

    Top-level (var so jQuery globalEval finds it):
        var client = window.client = function(config) {
            if (window._clientProfileInstance) return   // single-instance guard
            waitForElement('.client-container').then(() => {
                window._clientProfileInstance = new ClientProfile(config)
            })
        }

    ClientProfile class:
        init() calls: renderHeader, renderStats, renderTabs, renderContent,
            renderSidebar, attachEventListeners, initGlobalClickListener
            then: if editable is defined → initEditSwitch()

        renderHeader():
            Sets logo img, client name, rating stars, Top Pro badge.
            Logo click: only opens file picker when .edtable-mode class is present.
                On file selected → FileReader → img.src = base64
                wc.log then wc.publish('client:logo-change', { id, class, value, file })

        renderStats():
            Stats with type "team" AND leading number: splits into
                <span class="stat-num" data-editable data-stat-index="i"> + <span class="stat-suffix">
            All others: <span class="stat-text"> (static, no data-editable)

        renderContent():
            Sets all section titles and text from config.
            Calls renderSocialMedia()

        renderSocialMedia(forceEdit):
            isEdit = forceEdit if provided, else this.data.editable || window.edtable
            Review mode: shows icon links filtered to rows with url, hides #socialMediaTitle if none
            Edit mode: shows MD table (2 cols: icon + url input) + preview section (no "Preview" label)
                Table has thead: "Media" | "Your Social Link" (small caps gray)
                URL input: MD style, placeholder "Your social media link" italic gray
                Typing URL → icon opacity 1, preview updates live
                URL cleared → icon opacity 0.4, removed from preview
                Injected CSS for placeholder: font-style italic, color #bbb

        renderSidebar():
            Sets contactPrice, btnEstimate text (no viewDetailsLink).
            Hides onlineStatus if !isOnline.
            Sets guaranteeTitle, guaranteeText, learnMoreLink.

        initEditSwitch():
            Shows #editModeBar (display:flex)
            Uses cloneNode(true) on saveBtn to strip all previous listeners before adding new one
            Start state: toggle.checked = !!(config.editable || window.edtable)
            Apply switch style: slider blue + knob right when edit, gray + knob left when review
            Toggle change → enableEditable() or disableEditable(), show/hide saveBtn
            "Review" / "Edit" label clicks → set toggle.checked + dispatch change event
            Save Changes click:
                Collects all [data-editable] textContent (skipping socialMediaLinks, clientLogo, stat-index)
                Collects stats by data-stat-index
                Collects social URLs from .social-url inputs
                Collects logo base64 if src starts with data:
                wc.log then wc.publish('client:save', changes)
                Switches to review mode (toggle.checked=false, _applyEditSwitchStyle, disableEditable)
                Visual feedback: "Saved ✓" green for 2 seconds

        enableEditable():
            Adds .edtable-mode class to .client-container
            Calls renderSocialMedia(true)
            All [data-editable]: outline 2px dashed #009fd9, contenteditable=true, cursor text
            Logo exception: pointer cursor, title "Click to change photo", no contenteditable
            On blur: wc.log then wc.publish('client:edtable-change', { id, class, value })

        disableEditable():
            Removes .edtable-mode class from .client-container
            Removes contenteditable, outline, cursor, color, fontWeight, title from [data-editable]
            Calls renderSocialMedia(false)
            Calls renderStats() to regenerate clean HTML

        attachEventListeners():
            btnEstimate click → sets .nala-uid hidden field from config.nalaUID
                wc.log then wc.publish('mtk-request:open')
            btnShare click → navigator.share or alert
            Tab clicks → active class
            Global click listener: commented out console.log

        initGlobalClickListener():
            document click → wc.publish('global.click', clickData)
            console.log commented out


FILE: client/css/client.scss

    @import "../../css/nala.scss";
    body: margin-top 25px, margin-bottom 25px
    .client-container: margin 25px auto
    .stat-num: color $color-text-primary, font-weight medium (review mode default)
    .stat-suffix, .stat-text: color $color-text-primary (review mode default)
    .edtable-mode .stat-suffix, .edtable-mode .stat-text: color $color-text-secondary (lighter in edit)
    .edtable-mode .stat-num: color $color-text-primary (stays dark in edit)


FILE: client/js/mtk-request.config.js

    window.mtkRequestConfig = {
        title: "Contact Information",
        submitText: "Submit Request",
        fields: {
            name:    { label, placeholder: "e.g. John A. Smith",         required: true  },
            email:   { label, placeholder: "e.g. john@example.com",      required: false },
            phone:   { label, placeholder: "e.g. (646) 555-1234",        required: false },
            address: { label, placeholder: "e.g. 123 Main St, New York", required: false },
            help:    { label, placeholder: "e.g. Locked out...",          required: true  }
        },
        contactOptions: [ {email}, {phone} ],
        phoneTimes: [ morning, afternoon, evening ]
    }


FILE: client/js/mtk-request.js

    Entire file wrapped in: if (typeof MtkRequest === 'undefined') { ... }
    Instantiation: if (!window._mtkRequestInstance) { window._mtkRequestInstance = new MtkRequest() }

    render():
        Sets modal title and submit label from config
        Sets field labels and placeholder attributes from config
        Float labels: add class 'active' immediately on any field with a non-empty placeholder
        Builds radio buttons dynamically from contactOptions
        Builds call-time select from phoneTimes

    Placeholder style: font-size 12px, italic, color #bbb

    Validation on submit (strict order):
        1. Name blank                              → flag name
        2. contactType is phone AND phone blank    → flag phone
        3. contactType is email AND email blank    → flag email
        4. Both email AND phone blank              → flag email
        5. Email filled but invalid format         → flag email
        6. Phone filled but invalid US format      → flag phone
        7. Help blank                              → flag help

    flagField(input): red border + label, focus, clears on next input, wc.log each failure

    Payload: { nalaUID, name, email, phone, address, help, contactType, callTime, submittedAt, source }
    wc.log then wc.publish('mtk-request:submit', data)
    subscribe() to 'mtk-request:open' → bsModal.show()


FILE: client/css/mtk-request.scss

    Bootstrap modal wrapper
    Material Design floating labels (.md-field + .active)
    Radio group: flex-direction row (horizontal)
    Phone-times hidden by default, shown via .active class
    Placeholder: font-size 12px, italic, color #bbb


CRITICAL RULES

    1.  client.js loads in index.html BEFORE the wc-include — defines window.client before
        jQuery fetches and evals client.config.js

    2.  client.config.js is the LAST script inside client.html — calls client(config)
        after DOM is injected

    3.  mtk-request dialog is INLINED in client.html — never nested wc-include

    4.  MtkRequest wrapped in typeof guard — prevents re-declaration on reload

    5.  ClientProfile guarded by window._clientProfileInstance — prevents multiple instances
        and duplicate event listeners (root cause of multiple "Save Changes" invocations)

    6.  Save Changes uses cloneNode(true) on the button before attaching listener —
        strips all previous listeners regardless of how many times initEditSwitch runs

    7.  nalaUID flow: config.nalaUID → btnEstimate click sets .nala-uid hidden field
        → mtk-request submit reads it → published in payload

    8.  Validation order: contact-type-driven first, then OR check, then format, then help

    9.  Edit/review state tracked via .edtable-mode class on .client-container —
        CSS handles visual differences, not inline styles

    10. Logo only clickable in edit mode (.edtable-mode present)

    11. Every wc.publish() is always preceded by wc.log()

    12. SCSS only — never edit compiled .css directly

    13. client/css/client.scss imports: @import "../../css/nala.scss"
